snippet: Earnings appeared to reassure investors that the company’s profit margins were finally starting to improve.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO, April 17 — Intel’s first-quarter earnings appeared to reassure investors Tuesday that the company’s profit margins were finally starting to improve after a period of price cutting and heavy spending.

headline.main: Intel Earnings Jump Sharply in the Quarter, but Sales Dip
headline.print_headline: Intel Earnings Jump Sharply In the Quarter, But Sales Dip
